theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 11.1"
shows  "floor x + 2 * floor (0.5 * x) = 21"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor + 2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor .$ The final Answer is 21
 ### Proof
 Since $11 < 11.1 < 12$ we have $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor = 11.$  Next we have that  $2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = 2 \lfloor 5.55 \rfloor = 2 \cdot 5 = 10.$ Therefore, $\lfloor 11.1 \rfloor + 2 \cdot \lfloor 0.5 \cdot 11.1 \rfloor = \boxed{21}.$
 *)

theorem
fixes x :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 11.1"
shows  "floor x + 2 * floor (0.5 * x) = 21"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
